between the optical and X-rays as is\nobserved in other middle-aged pulsars. The thermal emission from the entire\nsurface of the neutron star likely dominates over the nonthermal emission in\nthe UV range. Observations of the PSR J0357+3205 in this range are promising to\nput more stringent constraints on its thermal properties.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Feb 2014 19:35:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-14"}
