and rapidity, over the\nranges p_T<15 GeV/c and 2.0<y<4.5. The total cross-sections in this kinematic\nregion, assuming unpolarised production, are measured to be sigma(pp ->\nUpsilon(1S) X) x B(Upsilon(1S) -> mu+mu-) = 1.111 +/- 0.043 +/- 0.044 nb,\nsigma(pp -> Upsilon(2S) X) x B(Upsilon(2S) -> mu+mu-) = 0.264 +/- 0.023 +/-\n0.011 nb, sigma(pp -> Upsilon(3S) X) x B(Upsilon(3S) -> mu+mu-) = 0.159 +/-\n0.020 +/- 0.007 nb, where the first uncertainty is statistical and the second\nsystematic.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Feb 2014 15:54:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 24 Apr 2014 15:18:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-26"}
